      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The speech channel on which speech is to be paused.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "chan"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A constant indicating when speech processing should be paused. Pass the constant ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "kImmediate",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " to pause immediately, even in the middle of a word. Pass ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "kEndOfWord",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " or ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "kEndOfSentence",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " to pause speech at the end of the current word or sentence, respectively. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "whereToPause"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A resultcode. See ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/applicationservices/speech_synthesis_manager#1659745",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "PauseSpeechAt",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functionmakes speech production pause at a specified point in the text. ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "PauseSpeechAt",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " returnsimmediately, although speech output will continue until the specifiedpoint.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can determine whether your application has paused speechoutput on a speech channel by obtaining a speech status informationstructure through the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function.While a speech channel is paused, the speech status informationstructure indicates that ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "outputBusy",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "outputPaused",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " areboth ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "TRUE",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If the end of the input text buffer is reached before thespecified pause point, speech output pauses at the end of the buffer.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "PauseSpeechAt",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functiondiffers from the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "StopSpeech",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "StopSpeechAt",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functionsin that a subsequent call to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "ContinueSpeech",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ",described next, causes the contents of the current text buffer tocontinue being spoken.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "If you plan to continue speech synthesis from a paused speechchannel, the text buffer being processed must remain available atall times and must not move while the channel is in a paused state. ",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
